.TH "strglobmatch" 9 "strglobmatch" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
strglobmatch \- glob expression pattern matching
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" strglobmatch
.BI "(const char *str "  ","
.BI "const char *pat "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "str" 12
the target string to match
.IP "pat" 12
the pattern string to match
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This returns true if the \fIstr\fP matches \fIpat\fP. \fIpat\fP can includes wildcards
('*','?') and character classes ([CHARS], complementation and ranges are
also supported). Also, this supports escape character ('\') to use special
characters as normal character.
.SH "NOTE"
if \fIpat\fP syntax is broken, this always returns false.
